<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-19T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="482" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d482">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/261c</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-19T18:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 19, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>6940. Most urgent. We have been prepared since yesterday to take over
                                Dutch ships and cannot understand your failure to advise us either
                                that we are free to take this action or that an agreement has been
                                reached in accordance with ultimatum expiring on the 18th. We regard
                                continued delay and uncertainty as very harmful and we desire to
                                take final action at once. Please give immediate reply.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>